data.chText: 分开；分隔；分配；（分出来的）部分
data.enText: the process or result of dividing into separate parts; the process or result of dividing sth or sharing it out
the division of labour between the sexes

data.chText: 时间和资源的合理分配
data.enText: a fair division of time and resources

data.chText: 把人口分成不同的年龄组
data.enText: the division of the population into age groups
the process of dividing one number by another
a disagreement or difference in opinion, way of life, etc., especially between members of a society or an organization

data.chText: 党内对于这场战争存在着严重的分歧。
data.enText: There are deep divisions in the party over the war.

data.chText: 弥合社会内部分歧的工作
data.enText: the work of healing the divisions within society

data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.enText: a large and important unit or section of an organization

data.chText: （英国体育运动，尤指足球比赛的）级

data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.enText: (in Britain) one of the group of teams that a sport competition is divided into, especially in football ( soccer )

data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.enText: a unit of an army, consisting of several brigades or regiments

data.chText: 他们的土地与我们的土地之间以一道树篱隔开。
data.enText: A hedge forms the division between their land and ours.
the separation of members of the British parliament into groups to vote for or against sth

data.chText: 议案未经分组表决就宣读通过了。
data.enText: The Bill was read without a division.

simple_means.memory_skill: divide 划分 + sion 行为，行为的过程和结果 → 分开

tr: the act or process of dividing
the act of dividing or partitioning
separation by the creation of a boundary that divides or keeps apart
an arithmetic operation that is the inverse of multiplication
the quotient of two numbers is computed
one of the portions into which something is regarded as divided and which together constitute a whole
example: the written part of the exam
the finance section of the company

tr: an army unit large enough to sustain combat
example: two infantry divisions were held in reserve

tr: a group of ships of similar type
a unit of the United States Air Force usually comprising two or more wings
an administrative unit in government or business
(botany) taxonomic unit of plants corresponding to a phylum
(biology) a group of organisms forming a subdivision of a larger category

example: he played baseball in class D for two years
Princeton is in the NCAA Division 1-AA

value.def: The division of a large unit into two or more distinct parts is the act of separating it into these parts.

example.ex: ...the unification of Germany, after its division into two states at the end of World War Two.
example.tran: 二战结束时曾被一分为二的德国实现了统一

gramarinfo.label: oft with poss, oft N <l>into</l> pl-n

value.def: The division of something among people or things is its separation into parts which are distributed among the people or things.

example.ex: The current division of labor between workers and management will alter.
example.tran: 当前工人与管理部门的分工将会改变。

value.def: Division is the arithmetical process of dividing one number into another number.

example.ex: I taught my daughter how to do division at the age of six.
example.tran: 女儿6岁时我就教她如何做除法了。

value.def: A division is a significant distinction or argument between two groups, which causes the two groups to be considered as very different and separate.

example.ex: The division between the prosperous west and the impoverished east remains.
example.tran: 繁荣的西部和贫穷的东部之间的差距仍然存在。

value.def: In a large organization, a division is a group of departments whose work is done in the same place or is connected with similar tasks.

example.tran: 该银行的拉丁美洲分部

value.def: A division is a group of military units which fight as a single unit.

example.ex: Several armoured divisions are being moved from Germany.
example.tran: 正从德国调动几个装甲师。

value.def: In the British Parliament, a division is a vote where the Members of Parliament go into separate rooms in order to record their vote.

In some sports, such as football, baseball, and basketball, a division is one of the groups of teams which make up a league. The teams in each division are considered to be approximately the same standard, and they all play against each other during the season.

example.ex: Villa had just been relegated from the First Division.
example.tran: 维拉队刚刚从甲级联赛中降级。

example.ex: ...the Scottish Premier Division leaders, Dundee United.
example.tran: 苏格兰超级联赛的领头羊，邓迪联队

value.tran: (足球等体育运动中联赛的)级

partsOfSpeech.dec: ad 做… + vis 看 + e → 使〔别人〕看到 → 劝告
ad 做… + vis 看 + ory …的 → 劝告的
en 使… + vis 看 + age 表行为 → 看 → 想象
e 出 + vid 看 + ence 性质，状态，行为 → 证据
e 出 + vid 看 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 看出来了 → 明显的
im 不 + provident 深谋远虑的 → 没有远见的，有钱就花 → 浪费的
in 使… + vid 看 + ious …的 → 让人看 →〔易〕招嫉妒的
pre 预先 + vis 看 + e → 预先看 → 预知
pro 在前 + vid 看 + e → 提前看好 → 预备
pro 向前 + vid 看 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 向前看的 → 有远见的 → 深谋远虑的
pro 向前 + vision 眼界 + al …的 → 眼前的 → 临时的
re 一再 + vis 看 + e → 一看再看 → 一改再改 → 修正
re 一再 + vis 看 + ion，revise 的名词 → 修正；校订本
super 上 + vis 看 + e → 在上面看 → 监督
vis 看 + ible 可…的 → 可见的
vis 看 + ion 表名词 → 视力；眼界
vision 视力；眼界 + ary …的 → 幻想的
vis 看 + ual 有…性质的 → 视力的
visual 视力的 + ize …化 → 使〔大家〕看到 → 使具体化
de 加强 + vis 分开 + e → 由古义“分开”转化而来
di 二 + vid 分开 + e → 一分为二 → 分开
di 二，两 + vis 分开 + ion 表名词 → 分开
di 二，两 + vid 分开 + end 表抽象名词 → 一变二，二变多 → 股息
in 不 + di 二，两 + vid 分开 + ual 有…性质的 → 不能分开的 → 个人的
